From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Build patch <noreply@localhost>
Date: Wed, 12 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Relax transformers version constraint for >=5.3

vLLM 0.17.1 already has code paths for transformers 5.x:
- vllm/transformers_utils/config.py checks Version("5.0.0")
- vllm/model_executor/models/transformers/base.py requires >=5.0 for Eagle3
The upper bound < 5 in requirements is overly conservative.
---
 requirements/common.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/requirements/common.txt b/requirements/common.txt
index a8e1450fa..d26d10481 100644
--- a/requirements/common.txt
+++ b/requirements/common.txt
@@ -7,7 +7,7 @@ requests >= 2.26.0
 tqdm
 blake3
 py-cpuinfo
-transformers >= 4.56.0, < 5
+transformers >= 5.3
 tokenizers >= 0.21.1  # Required for fast incremental detokenization.
 protobuf >= 5.29.6, !=6.30.*, !=6.31.*, !=6.32.*, !=6.33.0.*, !=6.33.1.*, !=6.33.2.*, !=6.33.3.*, !=6.33.4.* # Required by LlamaTokenizer, gRPC. CVE-2026-0994
 fastapi[standard] >= 0.115.0 # Required by FastAPI's form models in the OpenAI API server's audio transcriptions endpoint.
